name: Big Logo - Mens
description:
The Growl & Grandeur Logo is all important, so important in fact that we've gone out of our way & had it legally registered as a trademark. This entitles us to whack little ™'s all over the shop. We don't often bother because the pokey little ™ button is a sod to find on a keyboard. But don't let that fool you into thinking Growl & Grandeur means any less to us, copy it & we'll take legal action on your ass. Or send a bloke round to set a bloody big angry dog on you!

name: Matryoshka - Ladies
description:
Many call these little Russian nesting dolls Babushkas, where in fact ‘Babushka’ actually means old woman or granny in ye olde Russian & in turn babushka is also a western nickname for a headscarf tied below the chin, like how they do over in Eastern Europe. Whereas in the land of bears & vodka they are known simply as Matryoshka. Wikipedia is full of handy information, isn’t it?!

name: Pusher - Mens
description:
One afternoon in the late 1940s when Pacific was as flat as a blueberry pancake, disgruntled Californian surfers glued some roller skate wheels to pieces of an old wooden milk crate & invented skateboarding. Since then the sport has come a long way, what with proper boards & proper tricks. We admire people who belt across crumbly bits of concrete on a battered bit of plywood with wheels bolted to it's undercarriage. Skating is all about trial & error, until you master the craft, which is handy because we, at Growl & Grander, are proper crap at it!

Designed & produced in the UK

name: Swallows - Mens
description:

In days gone by sailing these great distances was extremely difficult and treacherous business, so one or more swallow tattoos denoted a bloody good seafarer! Legend is it, that if the sailor drowns, the swallows will carry their soul to heaven.
